# SPT#58 – Emergency Alarm Shut Down Machine

## Issue
- Machine: EQSPT00058  
- Model: C10.5  
- Problem: Emergency alarm → machine shutdown  
- Time: 01-Jul-2026 04:40 AM  
- Impact: 2 sputter trays (336 pcs)  

---

## Timeline
- 30-Jun 20:20 → Perform FAI → OK  
- 01-Jul 04:40 → Machine shut down  
- 01-Jul 05:00 → EQ check power supply & machine condition  
- 01-Jul 06:10 → Found EMO button pressed at unloader  
- 01-Jul 07:30 → Machine recovery → run normal  

---

## Symptom
- Machine shut down suddenly  
- No prior machine alarm related to equipment failure  
- Electrical system partially still active  

---

## Root Cause
1. Power supply at front cabinet disconnected  
2. Rear power (380V / 220V) still normal  
3. EMO button at unloader was pressed  
4. Root cause confirmed:  
   -> Operator pressed Emergency Stop  

---

## Failure Mechanism
- EMO button triggers safety circuit  
- Immediate shutdown of machine control  
- Stops operation regardless of machine status  
- Safety design overrides all process conditions  

---

## Actions
1. Check electrical power supply → OK  
2. Inspect emergency buttons  
3. Identify EMO pressed at unloader  
4. Reset EMO  
5. Restart machine  
6. PD test tray → OK  

---

## Corrective Action
1. Recover machine and verify operation  
2. Remove 2 trays for inspection / rework  

---

## Preventive Action
1. Check CCTV to identify who pressed EMO  
2. Train operator on EMO usage  
3. Consider adding cover or protection for EMO  

---

## Current Status
- Machine recovered  
- Test tray OK  
- Production resumed  

---

## Impact
- Quality: 2 trays affected  
- Production: ~3 hours downtime  
- Safety: EMO function normal  
- Repeat risk: HIGH if operator misuse continues  

---

## Open Risk / Follow-up
- CCTV investigation required  
- Operator discipline control  
- EMO accessibility review  

---

## Evidence
- Timeline confirms no equipment fault  
- EMO button found pressed  
- Power system normal  
- Machine recovered after reset  
